@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "What is QR Code?";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1 class="text-center animate__animated animate__fadeInDown">What is a QR Code?</h1>

    <p class="mt-4 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
        A <strong>QR Code</strong> (Quick Response Code) is a type of two-dimensional barcode that can be scanned using smartphones and other devices to quickly access digital content — like websites, contact info, Wi-Fi passwords, and much more.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-5 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">📌 Where Did QR Codes Come From?</h3>
    <p class="mt-3 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
        QR codes were invented in 1994 by a Japanese company called Denso Wave to track automotive parts during manufacturing. Since then, they’ve evolved into a versatile tool used worldwide — from scanning menus in cafes to verifying event tickets or making payments.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-5 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">✨ Why Are QR Codes So Popular?</h3>
    <ul class="mt-3 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
        <li><strong>Fast & Easy:</strong> Just point your phone’s camera and boom — you’re there.</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-purpose:</strong> Link to a website, share a file, send a payment, or even join a Wi-Fi network.</li>
        <li><strong>Contactless:</strong> Essential in the post-COVID era for safer interactions.</li>
        <li><strong>Eco-friendly:</strong> Reduce the need for paper by going digital.</li>
        <li><strong>Customizable:</strong> You can design QR codes with colors, logos, or creative patterns.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-5 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">🔍 What Can a QR Code Store?</h3>
    <ul class="mt-3 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
        <li>Website URLs</li>
        <li>Text messages or notes</li>
        <li>Email addresses</li>
        <li>Phone numbers</li>
        <li>Social media profiles</li>
        <li>vCards (contact information)</li>
        <li>Wi-Fi credentials</li>
        <li>Event details</li>
        <li>Payment requests</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-5 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">📲 How to Scan a QR Code</h3>
    <p class="mt-3 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
        Most modern smartphones can scan QR codes directly using the built-in camera. Just open your camera app and point it at the code — a link or action will appear. Alternatively, you can use a free QR scanner app.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-5 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">💡 Real-Life Use Cases</h3>
    <ul class="mt-3 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
        <li><strong>Restaurants:</strong> Digital menus and contactless ordering.</li>
        <li><strong>Retail:</strong> Coupons, product info, and loyalty programs.</li>
        <li><strong>Education:</strong> Share links to course materials or sign-in forms.</li>
        <li><strong>Events:</strong> E-tickets, check-ins, or promotional content.</li>
        <li><strong>Business Cards:</strong> Scan to save contact details instantly.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-5 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">🛡️ Are QR Codes Safe?</h3>
    <p class="mt-3 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
        QR codes themselves are safe, but just like any link, they can lead to harmful websites. Always scan from trusted sources and double-check the URL before clicking.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-5 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">🚀 Want to Make Your Own?</h3>
    <p class="mt-3 animate__animated animate__fadeInUp">
        That’s what this website is for! Head over to our <a asp-action="Index" asp-controller="QRCode">QR Code Generator</a> to create your own in seconds — free, fast, and privacy-friendly.
    </p>
</div>
